cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

The paper deals with automated segmentation of retinal blood vessels in fundus images using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also employs unsupervised hierarchical feature learning using stacked autoencoders, which falls under the category of deep learning and machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. The use of ensemble learning and multiple strategies for 2-level fusion of ensemble members suggests the involvement of neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with medical image analysis, which falls under the category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
